From fc480f1db3a486a701b4660204876336d8dee2e7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 09:23:59 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 22/39] WIP: media: dvb-frontends: avl6862: annotate
 intentional fall-through in i2c reg helpers

The reg_size switch statements in avl6862_i2c_wr_reg() and
avl6862_i2c_rd_reg() deliberately fall through to assemble the multi-byte
register value. Add the fallthrough; pseudo-keyword to silence the
-Wimplicit-fallthrough warnings.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Signed-off-by: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/media/dvb-frontends/avl6862.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/avl6862.c b/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/avl6862.c
index e7427be59265..0d8aeb027f13 100644
--- a/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/avl6862.c
+++ b/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/avl6862.c
@@ -149,8 +149,10 @@ static int avl6862_i2c_wr_reg(struct avl6862_priv *priv, u32 addr, u32 data,
 	case 4:
 		*(p++) = (u8)(data >> 24);
 		*(p++) = (u8)(data >> 16);
+		fallthrough;
 	case 2:
 		*(p++) = (u8)(data >> 8);
+		fallthrough;
 	case 1:
 	default:
 		*(p++) = (u8)(data);
@@ -187,8 +189,10 @@ static int avl6862_i2c_rd_reg(struct avl6862_priv *priv, u32 addr, u32 *data,
 	case 4:
 		*data |= (u32)(*(p++)) << 24;
 		*data |= (u32)(*(p++)) << 16;
+		fallthrough;
 	case 2:
 		*data |= (u32)(*(p++)) << 8;
+		fallthrough;
 	case 1:
 	default:
 		*data |= (u32) * (p);
